    "description": "<p>Each object in a 20-foot cube within range is outlined in light (your choice of color). Any creature in the area when the spell is cast is also outlined unless it makes a Dexterity saving throw. Until the spell ends, affected objects and creatures shed dim light in a 10-foot radius.</p><p>Any attack roll against an affected object or creature has advantage. The spell also negates the benefits of invisibility on affected creatures and objects.</p><hr class=\"a5e-rule u-my-md\"><p><strong>Rare: Rattling Faerie Fire.</strong> When an affected creature is damaged by a weapon attack it takes 1d4 psychic damage and is rattled until the end of its next turn. </p><p></p>",
